# Lab Next: **Custom Image + Custom Helm Chart ke Azure Container Registry OCI**

On fait l'envs production:

```
Custom App Code
   |
   v
Build Docker Image pakai ACR Task
   |
   v
Push image à Azure Container Registry
   |
   v
Package Helm chart fait soi-meme
   |
   v
Push Helm chart à ACR etre OCI artifact
   |
   v
Deploy à AKS de ACR
```

le skill important pour  **Helm + AKS expert**.

---

## 1. Set variable

```bash
RG=rg-aks-lab
AKS=aks-lab
LOC=southeastasia
ACR=acrbro$RANDOM$RANDOM
```

Check AKS:

```bash
kubectl get nodes
```
---

## 2. Créer Azure Container Registry

```bash
az acr create \
  --resource-group $RG \
  --name $ACR \
  --sku Basic \
  --location $LOC
```

Check:

```bash
az acr show -n $ACR -o table
```

---

## 3. Attach ACR à AKS

Pour que  node AKS puisse  pull private image de ACR.

```bash
az aks update \
  --resource-group $RG \
  --name $AKS \
  --attach-acr $ACR
```

---

## 4. Créer soi-meme le custom app image 

de repo parent égale à le repo `broapp`, Créer le repo app:

```bash
mkdir -p app
```

Créer `index.html`:

```bash
cat > app/index.html <<'EOF'
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Broapp AKS</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Halo bro, ini app sendiri dari ACR + Helm OCI + AKS</h1>
  <p>Image custom, chart custom, deploy ke Kubernetes Azure.</p>
</body>
</html>
EOF
```

Créer `Dockerfile`:

```bash
cat > app/Dockerfile <<'EOF'
FROM nginx:1.27-alpine
COPY index.html /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html
EXPOSE 80
EOF
```

Build image direct à ACR, on n' as besoin le  Docker local:

```bash
az acr build \
  --registry $ACR \
  --image broapp:v1 \
  ./app
```

Check image:

```bash
az acr repository list -n $ACR -o table
az acr repository show-tags -n $ACR --repository broapp -o table
```

---

## 5. Package Helm chart soi-meme

Assurer le repo  chart s'appelle `broapp`.

```bash
helm lint ./broapp
```

Prendre le chart version:

```bash
CHART_VERSION=$(awk '/^version:/ {print $2}' broapp/Chart.yaml | tr -d '"')
echo $CHART_VERSION
```

Package:

```bash
helm package ./broapp
```

Output est:

```text
broapp-0.2.0.tgz
```

---

## 6. Login Helm à ACR OCI

Utiliser token, assurer le secu pour  Cloud Shell:

```bash
TOKEN=$(az acr login --name $ACR --expose-token --output tsv --query accessToken)

echo $TOKEN | helm registry login $ACR.azurecr.io \
  --username 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000 \
  --password-stdin
```

---

## 7. Push Helm chart à ACR

```bash
helm push broapp-$CHART_VERSION.tgz oci://$ACR.azurecr.io/helm
```

Cek chart dari ACR:

```bash
helm show chart oci://$ACR.azurecr.io/helm/broapp --version $CHART_VERSION
```

---

## 8. Deploy à AKS de ACR OCI

Maintenant Helm chart est appris de ACR, image aussi de ACR.

```bash
helm upgrade --install bro-release \
  oci://$ACR.azurecr.io/helm/broapp \
  --version $CHART_VERSION \
  -n demo-acr \
  --create-namespace \
  --set image.repository=$ACR.azurecr.io/broapp \
  --set image.tag=v1 \
  --set service.type=LoadBalancer \
  --atomic \
  --wait \
  --timeout 10m
```

Check:

```bash
helm list -n demo-acr
kubectl get all -n demo-acr
kubectl get svc -n demo-acr
```

Attend  External IP:

```bash
kubectl get svc -n demo-acr -w
```

Ouvrir:

```text
http://EXTERNAL-IP
```

---

## 9. Helm test

```bash
helm test bro-release -n demo-acr --logs
```

Si success, c'est à dire le service est pu acceder de  cluster.

---

## 10. Simulation release v2

Changer app:

```bash
cat > app/index.html <<'EOF'
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Broapp AKS v2</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Broapp v2 release </h1>
  <p>Ini upgrade image via Helm à AKS.</p>
</body>
</html>
EOF
```

Build image v2:

```bash
az acr build \
  --registry $ACR \
  --image broapp:v2 \
  ./app
```

Upgrade release:

```bash
helm upgrade bro-release \
  oci://$ACR.azurecr.io/helm/broapp \
  --version $CHART_VERSION \
  -n demo-acr \
  --set image.repository=$ACR.azurecr.io/broapp \
  --set image.tag=v2 \
  --set service.type=LoadBalancer \
  --atomic \
  --wait \
  --timeout 10m
```

Check rollout:

```bash
kubectl rollout status deployment/bro-release-broapp -n demo-acr
helm history bro-release -n demo-acr
```

Si on veut faire le rollback:

```bash
helm rollback bro-release 1 -n demo-acr
```

